features: Qualcomm Quick Charge 3.0 - instead of pre-set voltage limits, QC 3.0 intelligently identifies the power needed and adjusts the charge rate to that which is most efficient. That means the device can charge faster (when it’s able to), and there’s up to 38% less power loss when charging.

Four Times Faster than conventional charger - using QC 3.0 allows your device to achieve 80% battery for only 30-35 minutes which is two times faster than the original Quick Charge standard. There is no need to wait for more than an hour just to charge your phone. [Read more in the description below]

Intelligent Negotiation for Optimum Voltage (INOV) - for optimum transfer as it maximizes the efficiency by letting the device detect the exact power level needed at any given time which allows your device to accumulate the required power levels.

Two USB Ports - allow you to simultaneously charge two devices at maximum speed. ATTANTION: 2 USB can be used together, However, the total output current should not exceed 3.5A, otherwise the IC will be automatically disconnected for protection.

The Perfect Travel Companion - the lightweight and compact size (plus all international voltage (AC110-240V) make it great cell phone charger for any your travel. Output: DC5V=2.4 amp (max); DC9V=1.5 amp (max); DC12V=1 amp (max)
description: USB charger for iphone, mobile phones and other 5V USB devices.
How Does Qualcomm Quick Charge 3.0 Work?

To help speed up the charge rate the voltage and amperage need to be adjusted. Since they’re both interconnected, and because there’s the component of resistance in there too, the ratios must be monitored and adjusted as the battery is “filled” with its charge.Think of this as filling a pitcher of water. You can fill it with a trickle of water and you won’t risk spilling a single drop – but it will take a long time. You can fill it with a firehose, but after a split-second burst there will be water everywhere, and after the hose is shut off, you’ll likely see that hardly any water stayed in the pitcher. Instead, as you fill a pitcher, you probably start out fairly slowly until the flow starts going, then gradually open the spigot all the way. As the water level starts getting to the top, you back off the flow rate to make sure you don’t overfill the pitcher and make a mess, eventually filling the last little bit with a trickle.That’s exactly how QC 3.0 works!A 3.0 charger “talks” with the device to coordinate the charge rate, and adjusts different voltage settings. All this results in “minimized losses, increased efficiency, and improved thermal performance.”
Why Charge Up to 80% Battery Life?
Smartphone batteries charge in two different phases:
The first phase is from 0-80% and this phase absorbs huge amount of power at once.
The first phase is from 0-80% and this phase absorbs huge amount of power at once.
From 81-100%, the battery has to be careful of the power level it absorbs.
From 81-100%, the battery has to be careful of the power level it absorbs.
QC 3.0 increases the process during the first phase four times faster than conventional chargers. Because of its algorithm, it can determine the power level it has to absorb when the phase changes.

description: Otterbox Defender MagGLASS UHD Screen Guard / iPhone XR 6.1"

Meet the UHD MagGLASS High-Performance Screen Guard. An A-spec tempered glass that is designed and engineered like your digital life  depends on it. We test and qualify our glass based on these 6 essential performance benchmarks:
1) A+ Impact Rating:

This is measured by the abilty for the glass (once installed) to retain structural integrity after a direct impact of 6FT.  Any glass chipping or hairlines fractures reduce the impact rating (and if larger than 0.02 in diameter disqualify it).
2) Screen Sensitivity:

IE Responsiveness. This is gauged in a side by side comparison of the touch input response time when used with/without  the glass installed. This metric is crucial to avoid the input delay (and frustration!) associated with lag-inducing screen guards.
3) Coverage:

Should be easy, right? We thought so. Though it might surprise you, nearly all well known screen protector brands we tried had  at least one display area that was left partially exposed once installed.
4) Screen Clarity:

This is where the MagGLASS really shines. The Ultra High Definition glass carries a total thickness of only 0.3mm, it's low profile  design aided by the embedded Pixel Grid Technology create an enjoyable, crystal clear user experience.
5) Scratch Resistance:

Our glass features a tough-as-nails true 9H hardness rating with dual tempered layering and reinforced shatterproof  construction - all to provide you with complete peace of mind regardless of the elements.
6) Ease of use:

Obvious yet important. Even the best glass in the world is useless without proper installation. Every MagGLASS set includes:  screen guard, micro fiber cloth, dust remover, alcohol pad, ensuring a perfect, bubble-free installation every time.

title: RadiArmor Anti-Radiation Detachable Wallet Case - Compatible with iPhone Xs Max - Lab Certified EMF Protection (Blue, XS Max)
features: OVERVIEW: RadiArmor has brought its EMF shielding technology to the larger size iPhone Xs Max with a 2-in-1 wallet case. The magnetically detachable bumper case is made of durable TPU rubber while the meticulously crafted wallet case is made from durable vegan leather and lined with our proprietary anti-radiation membrane.

LAB TESTED: RadiArmor cases are tested in a certified and independent laboratory using testing procedures that simulate a live phone call held to the ear. Our EMF material blocks over 99% of high frequency EMF and offers an effective EMF reduction of 91% during a call.

INTEGRITY: Many manufactures who claim 99% EMF protection are referring to the radiation blocking material, NOT the actual protection you receive on a call. If you covered your whole phone with EMF blocking material, then you'd have no signal. Our EMF blocking material is used on the front cover only, providing you real EMF protection with no sacrifice in reception.

FLEXIBILITY - This case uses ultrathin magnets that allow you to easily detach your phone from the wallet sleeve and still keep your phone protected. Using the wallet cover provides kickstand functionality and the ability to carry essential cards and cash in one place. Non-detachable version of this wallet case is also available under a separate listing.

DON'T BUY THE WRONG SIZE: This listing is for the detachable version of the larger size iPhone Xs MAX with a 6.5 inch (diagonally measured) screen. Other sizes as well as a non-detachable version of our wallet cases are available under separate listings and available in additional colors. NOTE: This case will not work with wireless chargers.
description: About RadiArmor
From anti-radiation headphones to EMF blocking phone cases, RadiArmor has been dedicated to helping people reduce their EMF exposure through science and technology.
Overview

RadiArmor’s anti-radiation material blocks over 99% of EMF radiation. However, since covering your entire phone with this material would result in no reception, only the front cover is lined with this material. This still provides an effective EMF reduction of 91% with no loss in reception. The front cover has a hole for sound to pass through so that you can close the case and talk at the same time.
Additional Features
Besides EMF shielding for your iPhone Xs Max, RadiArmor’s Anti-Radiation Wallet Case also provides:
3 Built-in Credit Card Pockets
3 Built-in Credit Card Pockets
1 Receipt/Cash Pocket
1 Receipt/Cash Pocket
RFID Protection of your Credit Cards
RFID Protection of your Credit Cards
Is there protection using this case when it’s in my pocket?
Yes, always be sure to have the front cover, where the anti-radiation material is applied, facing towards your body.
Why do you only make wallet cases?

The best way to block EMF is to put the EMF blocking material between you and the source. Some companies who claim EMF reduction put the material on the back of the phone. This would only increase your real-world exposure, not lower it.
What is EMF?

EMF or electromagnetic frequency is an invisible form of energy emitted by all electronic devices. The World Health Organization has classified EMF as a possible carcinogen and some people tend to be more sensitive to EMF than others.
NOTE:
If you have the most recent iPhone X, there is a default setting that disconnects a phone call when it detects a closed cover. To fix this, simply adjust your settings.
Go to Settings > Display & Brightness > LOCK > UNLOCK

This phone case has a sticky layer that consists of millions of nano sized suction cups, so when you stick it to a flat surface, make sure you wipe the surface clean and it is dust free; stick the case on the surface and push out any air that may be trapped inside. When the nano-suction case is pressed against a flat surface, millions of miniature suction cups create a large vacuum, generating a strong suction force that can hold a tremendous amount of weight.
The nature of the technology allows easy removal without residue, and makes it reusable. If the back of the case becomes dirty, simply use water to clean so one can reuse the case.

DO NOT STICK TO painted walls, trees, sofa, bumpy and dusty surfaces; it functions just like suction cup hooks that stick on bathroom walls or doors. This product will stick to glass, whiteboards, metal, kitchen cabinets or tile and smooth flat surfaces. This comes in handy if you wish to use it in a car for GPS purposes, or if you are watching a game or show while putting on makeup, shaving etc.

features: Convenient cigarette lighter adapter charges iPod while you drive

description: Product Description

Hit the road Jack! And don't you come back to recharge your iPod. Because this convenient Griffin auto charger lets you play your iPod on the road while giving it a constant charge whether you're playing music or in standby mode. The PowerPod is compatible with original FireWire iPods and newer dockable iPods. Pops easily into your vehicle's lighter. Includes a 4' FireWire cable with dock connection.
Amazon.com

Music fans love to take their iPods on the road, but the road offers one major problem--no charging outlets. Enter the Griffin PowerPod auto charger, which plugs into your car's cigarette lighter to provide a consistent power source. The charger powers the iPod whether it's playing music or in standby mode, so users don't have to suffer through any charging downtime. It's also intended to complement the iPod's sleek, modern design, with a dimpled white and grey body. The PowerPod comes with a 4-foot FireWire cable that connects to your iPod's dock connector for charging. Owners of the original 1G and 2G iPods can instead connect the default FireWire cables that came with their models.
Features and Performance

iPod owners will warm up to the PowerPod in a manner of seconds. It's ready to use right out of the box--just plug in the FireWire cable and start charging. A small red LED light indicates when the unit is working, as does the iPod's charging icon in the upper right corner. During testing, the PowerPod refreshed about an hour's worth of playtime in a few minutes while music was playing. Owners of other iPod auto accessories such as FM transmitters--which draw their power from the iPod's battery--will find the PowerPod particularly valuable, as it keeps their iPods juiced up over long road trips.
Simple and efficient, the PowerPod is a must for iPod-equipped road trippers.
--Rivers Janssen
